val","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","An unstable motorcycle may fall, causing injury to the operator or damage to the motorcycle.","Perform the following operations:","Disconnect the battery (see ","Battery - Removal",").","The rotor magnets are very strong. When handling the alternator cover the magnets may 'grab' the stator, causing injury to the hands or fingers. When handling the alternator cover wear suitable gloves and only grip the alternator cover by the outside surfaces; always keep hands and fingers clear when handling the alternator cover.","Raise and support the rear of the motorcycle under the frame or engine. Position a block to support the rear wheel.","Rear Wheel - Removal",".","Alternator Regulator/Rectifier - Removal","Remove the right hand side panel (see ","Side Panels",").","Front Sprocket Cover - Removal","Detach the two retaining clips securing the alternator harness to the ABS modulator bracket.","Note the alignment marks on the brake actuator arm and the brake pivot shaft for installation.","Note the position of the brake pedal return spring for installation.","Remove the pinch bolt securing the brake linkage to the brake pivot shaft.","Detach the brake linkage from the brake pivot shaft and collect the return spring.","Pinch bolt","Return spring","Brake pivot shaft alignment mark","Brake actuator arm alignment mark","Release the four fixings and position the rider control plate to one side.","Fixings","Rider control plate","Remove the two fixings securing the rear brake master cylinder plate to the cradle assembly. Support the master cylinder plate assembly.","Remove the cradle rear mounting fixings and collect the nut plate.","Cradle fixings","Control plate fixings","Right hand control plate","Remove the crankcase front mounting nut and bolt.","Remove the fixings securing the cradle assemblies to the headstock and collect the nut plate.","Fixings (to headstock)","Bolt (to crankcase front mounting)","Detach the cradle assembly from the lower mounting of the radiator and remove the cradle assembly.","Radiator lower mounting","Cradle assembly","Remove the right hand silencer (see ","Exhaust Silencer - Removal",").","Remove the lock nuts and detach the coolant expansion tank from its mounting. Discard the lock nuts. Position the tank to one side.","Lock nuts","Coolant expansion tank","Remove the lock nut and detach the rear brake fluid reservoir from the coolant expansion tank mounting plate and position aside. Discard the lock nut.","Rear brake fluid reservoir lock nut","Fixings","Alternator harness","Secure the rear brake fluid reservoir in an upright position.","To prevent paint damage, do not spill brake fluid onto any area of the bodywork. Spilled brake fluid will damage paintwork.","Release the two fixings and remove the coolant expansion tank mounting plate, unhooking the master cylinder hose from the retention feature.","Remove the chain from the front sprocket.","Release the uppermost fixing from the packaging cover and remove the intake shield.","Intake shield fixing","Intake shield","Packaging cover","Release the three fixings and remove the packaging cover.","Packaging cover","Fixings","Lower fixing","Release the two fixings and detach the starter solenoid bracket from the crankcase bracket.","Crankshaft position sensor electrical connector","Gear position sensor electrical connection","Starter motor cable","Starter motor solenoid","Starter solenoid bracket","Crankcase bracket","Note the routing of the crankshaft position sensor harness for installation.","Disconnect the crankshaft position sensor from the main harness.","Route the crankshaft position sensor harness through the harness guide on the crankcase.","Remove the fixing and detach the harness guide from the crankcase.","Fixing","Harness guide","Carefully remove the alternator harness from the harness guide.","Note the routing of the alternator harness and its clips for installation.","Route the alternator harness with the grey electrical connector to the alternator cover.","Place an oil catch tray beneath the alternator cover to collect any oil that may spill out on removal.","Release the fixings securing the alternator cover to the crankcases. ","Removal Sequence","Carefully withdraw the alternator cover from the crankcase.","Remove the gasket and clean the surfaces of the crankcase and the alternator cover using a lint free cloth.","Remove and discard the O-rings from the balancer dead shaft.","O-rings","Balancer dead shaft"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType05","createdAt":"2024-06-12T07:36:04.869Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-12T07:36:04.869Z","__v":0}